# Icon Standards

**Always** use proper SVG icons from the `react-icons` library. **Never** use emoji, unicode symbols, or text characters as icons (e.g. ✕, ↑, 🌿, ✓).

## Install

```bash
npm install react-icons
```

## Usage

```jsx
// ✅ GOOD — import from react-icons
import { FiSend, FiX, FiLeaf, FiArrowUp } from "react-icons/fi";
import { MdEco, MdVolunteerActivism } from "react-icons/md";

<FiSend size={18} />
<FiX size={16} />
```

```jsx
// ❌ BAD — never use emoji or unicode as icons
<button>↑</button>
<button>✕</button>
<span>🌿</span>
```

## Common Icon Sets

| Set | Import path | Use for |
|-----|-------------|---------|
| Feather | `react-icons/fi` | UI actions (send, close, search, arrow) |
| Material | `react-icons/md` | Eco/environment/general purpose |
| Heroicons | `react-icons/hi` | Navigation, status |
| Phosphor  | `react-icons/ph` | Modern UI accents |

## Sizing & Styling

```jsx
// Size via prop
<FiLeaf size={20} />

// Color via style or className
<FiLeaf size={20} style={{ color: "var(--accent)" }} />
```
